{"title_page": "Niles Canyon ghost", "text_new": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{unreliable sources|date=April 2012}}\n{{tone|date=April 2012}}\n{{no footnotes|date=April 2012}}\n}}\nITS ALL FAKE\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tracypress.com/view/full_story/2180762/article-Ghost-girl-of-Niles-Canyon-rests|title=Golden State Newspapers|website=Golden State Newspapers|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lovehaight.org/links/secret_sidewalk/white_witch.html|title=Welcome lovehaight.org - Hostmonster.com|website=www.lovehaight.org|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.strangeusa.com/Viewlocation.aspx?id=749|title=Niles Canyon Road Niles Canyon Road Pleasanton, Ca 94588 Alameda County Haunt|last=Montana|first=Matt|website=www.strangeusa.com|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref>\n*http://tracypress.com/view/full_story/2180762/article-Ghost-girl-of-Niles-Canyon-rests\n*http://www.strangeusa.com/Viewlocation.aspx?id=749\n*http://www.lovehaight.org/links/secret_sidewalk/white_witch.html\n\n[[Category:American ghosts]]\n[[Category:Female legendary creatures]]\n", "text_old": "{{Multiple issues|\n{{unreliable sources|date=April 2012}}\n{{tone|date=April 2012}}\n{{no footnotes|date=April 2012}}\n}}\n\nThe '''Niles Canyon ghost''' story is an [[urban legend]] based off of the [[vanishing hitchhiker]] archetype. There are many different variations of this story depending on whom you ask. All stories include a girl being involved in some sort of motorized vehicle accident on February 26 (year often changed). One variation of the story includes a girl being involved in a car crash on [[Niles Canyon]] road (off the [[Interstate 680 (California)|680 freeway]] in [[Sunol, California]]) on the way to her [[prom]]. The girl died on impact and to this day is said to haunt Niles Canyon road every February 26. The tale of the haunting goes that people traveling along Niles Canyon road (now [[California State Route 84|Highway 84]]) on the night of February 26 will see a normal-looking high school-aged girl walking along the road in a [[prom dress]] (many people have said it is white). People traveling along the road (mostly those traveling alone) have said to have stopped and offered the girl a ride. She accepts the ride, giving the driver an address across the bridge (either Dumbarton or Bay Bridge depending on the storyteller). Once the driver gets to the beginning of the bridge, the girl will disappear. Sometimes people have gone to the address to find that a girl many years ago matching that description once lived there. Today, many people will travel along this treacherous pitch black road in the hopes of catching a glimpse of the Niles Canyon ghost.\n\n== References ==\n{{Reflist}}<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://tracypress.com/view/full_story/2180762/article-Ghost-girl-of-Niles-Canyon-rests|title=Golden State Newspapers|website=Golden State Newspapers|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.lovehaight.org/links/secret_sidewalk/white_witch.html|title=Welcome lovehaight.org - Hostmonster.com|website=www.lovehaight.org|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=http://www.strangeusa.com/Viewlocation.aspx?id=749|title=Niles Canyon Road Niles Canyon Road Pleasanton, Ca 94588 Alameda County Haunt|last=Montana|first=Matt|website=www.strangeusa.com|access-date=2017-11-30}}</ref>\n*http://tracypress.com/view/full_story/2180762/article-Ghost-girl-of-Niles-Canyon-rests\n*http://www.strangeusa.com/Viewlocation.aspx?id=749\n*http://www.lovehaight.org/links/secret_sidewalk/white_witch.html\n\n[[Category:American ghosts]]\n[[Category:Female legendary creatures]]\n", "name_user": "140.82.173.93", "label": "vandal", "comment": "", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Niles_Canyon_ghost"}
{"title_page": "Amrutha Suresh", "text_new": "{{Use Indian English|date=March 2020}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=March 2020}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Amrutha Suresh\n| image         = <!-- filename only, no \"File:\" or \"Image:\" prefix, and no enclosing [[brackets]] -->\n| alt           = <!-- descriptive text for use by speech synthesis (text-to-speech) software -->\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = <!-- only use if different from name -->\n| birth_date    = {{Birth date and age|df=yes|1990|8|2}}\n| birth_place   = [[Kochi]], [[Kerala]], India\n| other_names   = Amritha Suresh, Ammu\n| occupation    = {{hlist|Singer|Composer|Radio Jockey|Model}}\n| years_active  = 2007 \u2013 present\n| spouse        = {{Marriage|[[Bala (actor)|Bala]]|2010|2019|reason=divorced}}\n| children      = 1\n| relatives     = [[Abhirami Suresh]] (sister)\n| website       = {{URL|amrutamgamay.com}}\n| module          = {{Infobox musical artist|embed=yes\n| background      = solo_singer\n| genre           = {{flatlist|\n* [[Pop music|Pop]]\n* [[Indian classical music|Classical]]\n* [[Folk music|Folk]]\n* [[Ghazal]]\n* [[Bhajan]]\n* [[Rock music|Rock]]\n}}\n| instrument      = Vocals \n| label           = Independent artist\n| associated_acts = Amrutam Gamay\n}}\n}}\n\n'''Amrutha Suresh''' (born 2 August 1990), also known '''Amritha Suresh''', is an Indian singer, composer, songwriter, and [[radio jockey]]. She attained popularity after her stint at the [[reality television]] singing competition ''[[Star Singer|Idea Star Singer]]'' on [[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]] in 2007. Since then, she has sang and composed in several films and music albums. She has been a celebrity radio jockey on [[Radio Suno 91.7]] with the music show ''Suno Melodies''. In 2014, she founded the [[Band (rock and pop)|music band]] Amrutam Gamay, in which Amrutha and her sister [[Abhirami Suresh]] are the lead vocalists. They are also known for [[vlogging]], with the series ''AG Vlogs'' on their YouTube channel ''Amrutam Gamay \u2013 AG''.\n\n==Early life==\nAmrutha was born on 2 August 1990 to musician P. R. Suresh and Laila.<ref>{{cite news|title=A Musical Love Story|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2012/may/07/a-musical-love-story-365437.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=7 May 2012}}</ref> Her father Suresh is a [[Hindu]] and mother Laila is a [[Christians|Christian]]. She has a sister, singer-composer [[Abhirami Suresh]], who is five years younger.<ref name=\"Vanitha1\">{{cite news|author=Shyama|title='\u0d0e\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d3e\u0d35\u0d7c\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d35\u0d47\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d47 \u0d05\u0d35\u0d30\u0d35\u0d30\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d46 \u0d1c\u0d40\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d24\u0d02 \u0d1c\u0d40\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d41\u0d33\u0d4d\u0d33 \u0d05\u0d35\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d36\u0d02'; \u0d35\u0d3f\u0d35\u0d3e\u0d26\u0d19\u0d4d\u0d19\u0d7e \u0d06\u0d18\u0d4b\u0d37\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d35\u0d30\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d4d \u0d05\u0d2e\u0d43\u0d24 \u0d1a\u0d4b\u0d26\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41|url=https://www.vanitha.in/celluloid/multiplex/amrutha-suresh-vanitha-interview.html|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[Vanitha]]|date=12 September 2019|language=ml}}</ref> They are from [[Edappally]], [[Kochi]].<ref name=\"travel\">{{cite news|title=Travel and music are two sides of a coin - Amrutha Suresh|url=https://travel.manoramaonline.com/travel/celebrity-travel/2018/07/05/singer-amrutha-suresh-travel-stories.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=5 July 2018}}</ref> Living in a family (paternal) of musicians inspired her to pursue music from a young age.<ref name=\"MM1\"/> Amrutha started singing at age three; [[Celine Dion]] and [[Michael Jackson]] are the singers who influenced her to become a singer.<ref name=\"FWD\">{{cite web|author=FWD media|title=Amrutha Suresh Is Back With A Breath Of New Life|url=https://www.fwdlife.in/amrutha-suresh-is-back-with-a-breath-of-new-life|publisher=FWD Life|accessdate=2 March 2020|date=28 July 2017}}</ref> Amrutha was a topper at schools.<ref name=\"Vanitha1\"/> Even though, she dropped 12th standard for contesting in the [[reality television]] singing competition ''[[Star Singer|Idea Star Singer]]'', later she completed the course in private.<ref>{{cite news|last=\u0d0e\u0d02.|first=\u0d2a\u0d41\u0d37\u0d4d\u0d2a|title=\u0d12\u0d30\u0d41 \u0d15\u0d02\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d32\u0d40\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d4d \u0d2e\u0d46\u0d2f\u0d4d\u200c\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d4b\u0d35\u0d31\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d4d \u0d1e\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d4d\u200d \u0d06\u0d17\u0d4d\u0d30\u0d39\u0d3f\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d24\u0d4d: \u0d05\u0d2e\u0d43\u0d24 \u0d38\u0d41\u0d30\u0d47\u0d37\u0d4d\u200c|url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/women/interview/amrutha-suresh-abhirami-music-1.2147731|accessdate=29 February 2020|work=[[Mathrubhumi]]|date=7 August 2017|language=ml}}</ref> She then took graduation in [[Bachelor of Business Administration]] (BBA) and post-graduation in [[Master of Business Administration]] (MBA), and also holds degrees in [[Carnatic music]] and [[Hindustani classical music]].<ref name=\"MM1\">{{cite news|last1=\u0d35\u0d3f\u0d1c\u0d2f\u0d7b|first=\u0d32\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d37\u0d4d\u0d2e\u0d3f|title=\u0d24\u0d4b\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d41\u0d2a\u0d4b\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d4d\u0d32; \u0d2a\u0d3e\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d1a\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d3f\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f \u0d35\u0d40\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d05\u0d2e\u0d43\u0d24 \u0d38\u0d41\u0d30\u0d47\u0d37\u0d4d|url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/music/interviews/2019/02/05/exclussive-interview-with-singer-amrita-suresh.html|accessdate=29 February 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=6 February 2019|language=ml}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\n===Music===\nComing from a musician's family, she used to perform at stage shows during her childhood. While studying in eighth standard, she has been a child singer in [[Nadirshah]]'s stage shows.<ref>{{cite news|title=\u0d35\u0d40\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d15\u0d3e\u0d7c \u0d35\u0d47\u0d23\u0d4d\u0d1f \u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e \u0d2c\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d27\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d23\u0d4d, \u0d05\u0d24\u0d46\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d24\u0d46\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d3e\u0d2f \u0d24\u0d40\u0d30\u0d41\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d28\u0d2e\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d30\u0d41\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41|url=https://www.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/news/amrutha-suresh-about-life-amrutha-suresh-singer-1.2761721|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[Mathrubhumi]]|date=23 April 2018|language=ml}}</ref> In 2007, Amrutha contested in the second season of [[reality television]] singing competition ''[[Star Singer|Idea Star Singer]]'' on [[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]], she was one of the popular contestants on the show.<ref>{{cite news|title=Sisters Amritha Suresh and Abhirami to feature in 'Paadam Namukku Paadam'|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/malayalam/sisters-amritha-suresh-and-abhirami-to-feature-in-paadam-namukku-paadam/articleshow/70450218.cms|accessdate=3 March 2020|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=30 July 2019}}</ref> It helped her foray into film industry. Since then, she has sang [[Playback singer|playback]] in a number of Malayalam films. ''[[Pulliman (2010 film)|Pulliman]]'' was her debut film as playback singer, composed by [[Sharreth]]. Her rendition of the song \"Munthirpoo\" from the film ''[[Aagathan]]'' (2010) was well received.<ref>{{cite news|author=\u0d38\u0d4d\u0d35\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d02 \u0d32\u0d47\u0d16\u0d15\u0d7b|title=\u0d08 \u0d2e\u0d4b\u0d21\u0d32\u0d3f\u0d19\u0d4d \u0d12\u0d30\u0d41 \u0d38\u0d4d\u0d35\u0d2a\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d02; \u0d17\u0d3e\u0d2f\u0d3f\u0d15 \u0d05\u0d2e\u0d43\u0d24 \u0d38\u0d41\u0d30\u0d47\u0d37\u0d3f\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46 \u0d15\u0d3f\u0d1f\u0d3f\u0d32\u0d7b \u0d2b\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d4b \u0d37\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d4d|url=https://www.manoramaonline.com/music/music-news/2017/07/28/amrutha-suresh-photo-shoot-is-stunning.html|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=28 July 2017|language=ml}}</ref>\n\nShe sang \"Kannu Karuthu\" for music director [[Sharreth]] in his album ''Strawberry Theyyam'' (2014) which was a blend of folk and western orchestration, the song was particularly praised in the 9-track album.<ref>{{cite news|last=M.|first1=Athira|title=When folk music goes pop|url=https://www.thehindu.com/features/metroplus/when-folk-music-goes-pop/article5962704.ece|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=30 April 2014}}</ref> In 2014, Amrutha founded the [[Band (rock and pop)|music band]] Amrutam Gamay. Amrutha and her sister [[Abhirami Suresh]] are the lead vocalists of the band. The band performed internationally at [[Gig (music)|gigs]] within six months of its formation.<ref name=\"TNIE1\">{{cite news|last=Menon|first1=Anoop|title=Sister Act|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/cities/thiruvananthapuram/2015/jul/24/Sister-Act-790595.html|accessdate=27 February 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=24 July 2015}}</ref> The band handles all kinds of genres, including Indian, western, folk, classical, or rock.<ref>{{cite web|last=Thankappan|first=Charishma|title=7 Up-and-Coming Bands From Kerala to Watch Out For|url=https://theculturetrip.com/asia/india/articles/7-up-and-coming-bands-from-kerala-to-watch-out-for/|publisher=The Culture Trip|accessdate=3 March 2020}}</ref> The band's [[cover version]] of Israeli folk song \"[[Hava Nagila]]\" sang by Amrutha was popular among the global Jewish community.<ref name=\"TNIE1\"/> The song gave her much appreciations.<ref>{{cite news|last=John|first=Binoo K.|title=In Kerala, the new revolutionaries are bands fusing classical, temple, folk and rock music|url=https://scroll.in/article/721399/in-kerala-the-new-revolutionaries-are-bands-fusing-classical-temple-folk-and-rock-music|accessdate=3 March 2020|work=[[Scroll.in]]|date=8 May 2015}}</ref> In 2015, Amrutha and Abhirami wrote and composed multiple original songs for their band, including \"Katturumbu\", \"Ayyayo\", and \"Harps of Peace\".<ref name=\"TNIE1\"/><ref>{{cite news|last=M.|first=Athira|title=Rocking the charts|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/young-female-musicians-are-rocking-the-charts/article7578673.ece|accessdate=26 February 2020|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=25 August 2015}}</ref>\n\nIn 2017, Amrutha released her first [[Single (music)|single]], \"Anayathe\", which featured herself and was themed at and was a tribute to motherhood and women.<ref>{{cite news|author=Express News Service|title=Sound of music|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2017/may/16/sound-of--music-1605526.html|accessdate=3 March 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=16 May 2017}}</ref> The song was positively received and garnered attention for its theme. After its release, Amrutha got acting offers from some [[Tamil cinema|Tamil films]], but she refused as she was not seeing herself as an actress at the time.<ref>{{cite news|last=Sreenivasan|first=Deepthi|title=Don't want to cry any more: Amrutha Suresh|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/music/180517/dont-want-to-cry-any-more-amrutha-suresh.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=18 May 2017}}</ref> She was also approached by a [[Canada|Canadian]] production company for an English film. In the same year, she began presenting the musical [[talk show]] ''Suno Melodies'' on [[Radio Suno 91.7]] as a celebrity [[radio jockey]].<ref name=\"Vanitha1\"/> Amrutha along with Abhirami composed, sang and acted in the title song of the film ''[[Crossroad (2017 film)|Crossroad]]'' that year. It was their debut composition in a film and was composed in a short notice.<ref>{{cite news|last=Manu|first=Meera|title=Suresh sisters on the go|url=https://www.deccanchronicle.com/entertainment/mollywood/130717/suresh-sisters-on-the-go.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[Deccan Chronicle]]|date=13 July 2017}}</ref> It was followed by a single in the film ''[[Aadu 2]]'' (2017), titled \"Aadu 2 \u2013 Success Song\".<ref name=\"TOI1\">{{cite news|last=Soman|first=Deepa|title=Amritha Suresh: The energy on stage helps me stay sane and happy|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/music/amritha-suresh-the-energy-on-stage-helps-me-stay-sane-and-happy/articleshow/69058172.cms|accessdate=29 February 2020|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=27 April 2019}}</ref>\n\nIn 2019, she sang \"Minni Minni\" in the film ''[[June (film)|June]]'' which was well received.<ref>{{cite news|author=Onmanorama staff|title=Music helped me to face life better: Amritha Suresh|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/music/2019/04/27/amrutha-suresh-on-life-and-music.html|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=27 April 2019}}</ref> For the song, she was nominated for the Mazhavil Music Award for Best Female Singer.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mazhavil Music Awards 2019 {{!}} Amrutha Suresh and Abhirami Suresh on Red Carpet ! {{!}} Mazhavil Manorama|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9QfDC69mAAY|publisher=[[Mazhavil Manorama]]|accessdate=2 March 2020|date=23 August 2019}}</ref> In the same year, Amrutha sang the first of the three [[music video]]s in DJ Savyo's ''Destiny'', an experimental album which used [[Shiva]] mantra in the backdrop of [[electronic dance music]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Mathews|first=Anna|title=DJ Savyo to release first song of Destiny|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/music/dj-savyo-to-release-first-song-of-destiny/articleshow/70617334.cms|accessdate=29 February 2020|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=10 August 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last=Kadiyala|first=Swetha|title=Tuning to vedic mantras|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2019/aug/24/tuning-to-vedic-mantras-2023433.html|accessdate=29 February 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=24 August 2019}}</ref> That year she also signed a project with [[Swedish people|Swedish]] musician Neil Luckz, who contacted her after watching her music video ''Ohm Nama Shivaya''; she is working on six English songs for the project.<ref name=\"TOI1\"/> In 2019, she sang a song in the children's film ''Sullu'' composed by Abhirami.<ref>{{cite news|last=Mathews|first=Anna|title=Sisters Amritha and Abhirami Suresh in a singing collaboration|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/malayalam/music/sisters-amritha-and-abhirami-suresh-in-a-singing-collaboration/articleshow/70619548.cms|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=10 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Other works===\nAmrutha is also into [[Model (person)|modelling]]. In 2017, she was featured in the cover of lifestyle magazine FWD Life.<ref name=\"FWD\"/> In the following year, she walked the ramp at Kerala Fashion Runway.<ref>{{cite web|author=Rakesh|title=Amrutha Suresh Singer Photos Stills Gallery|url=https://www.indiancinemagallery.net/photos/amrutha-suresh/view/image/amrutha-suresh-at-kerala-fashion-runway-2018-19/|publisher=Indian Cinema Gallery|accessdate=3 March 2020|date=11 July 2017}}</ref> She was also featured on the cover page of Vanitha Magazine along with her sister. In 2018, Amrutha started a [[Hashtag activism|hashtag campaign]] on [[Instagram]] known as Amazing Me, promoting self-esteem. It received positive response from public.<ref>{{cite web|last=Priya|first=Priyadharsini|title=\u0d28\u0d2e\u0d41\u0d15\u0d4d\u0d15\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d12\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d \u0d2a\u0d31\u0d1e\u0d4d\u0d1e\u0d41\u0d15\u0d42\u0d1f\u0d47 '\u0d05\u0d2e\u0d47\u0d38\u0d3f\u0d19\u0d4d \u0d2e\u0d40' \u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d4d! \u0d05\u0d2e\u0d43\u0d24\u0d2f\u0d41\u0d1f\u0d46 \u0d38\u0d46\u0d7d\u0d2b\u0d4d \u0d2e\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d4d\u0d1f\u0d3f\u0d35\u0d47\u0d37\u0d7b \u0d0f\u0d31\u0d4d\u0d31\u0d46\u0d1f\u0d41\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4d \u0d38\u0d48\u0d2c\u0d7c \u0d32\u0d4b\u0d15\u0d02|url=https://www.vanitha.in/justin/amazing-me-amritha-suresh-self-motivation-in-instagram.html|publisher=[[Vanitha]]|accessdate=3 March 2020|language=ml|date=26 November 2018}}</ref> In December 2018, Amrutha and her sister Abhirami started a [[YouTube]] channel, ''Amrutam Gamay \u2013 AG'', with the series ''AG Vlogs'' to publish their creative content.<ref>{{cite news|last=Varghese|first=Anuja Susan|title=Kerala's celebs connect with fans via YouTube content|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/states/kerala/2019/aug/04/keralas-celebs-connect-with-fans-via-youtube-content-2013860.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=4 August 2019}}</ref> The content is related to their personal lives, travel, food, music, shopping among other things.<ref>{{cite news|last=M.|first=Athira|title=Star-studded web|url=https://www.thehindu.com/entertainment/malayali-celebrities-with-their-youtube-channels/article25970284.ece|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[The Hindu]]|date=11 January 2019}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|author=Onmanorama staff|title=Amrutha Suresh back with vlog, recreates mother's old pic|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/2019/09/14/amrutha-suresh-ag-vlog-video-mother-old-pic.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=14 September 2019}}</ref> The series met with positive reception from viewers.<ref>{{cite news|author=Onmanorama staff|title=Going through the toughest phase of my life: Amrutha Suresh|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/entertainment/entertainment-news/2019/09/10/amrutha-suresh-on-ag-vlog-insta-post.html|accessdate=2 March 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=10 September 2019}}</ref> In 2020, Amrutha and Abhirami entered as contestants in the [[Bigg Boss (Malayalam season 2)|second season]] of Malayalam [[reality television]] game show ''[[Bigg Boss (Malayalam TV series)|Bigg Boss]]''. They entered the Bigg Boss house as wildcard entrants on day-50 and plays as a pair.<ref>{{cite news|title=Bigg Boss Malayalam 2: Siblings Amritha and Abhirami Suresh make a wild card entry in the house|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/malayalam/bigg-boss-malayalam-2-siblings-amritha-and-abhirami-suresh-make-a-wild-card-entry-in-the-house/articleshow/74275921.cms|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[The Times of India]]|date=24 February 2020}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nAmrutha first met her future husband [[Bala (actor)|Bala]] at the sets of the film ''Venalmaram'' in which he was starring and Amrutha was playback singer. Later, they developed a friendship-turned-romance while she was contesting in the [[reality TV]] singing competition ''[[Star Singer|Idea Star Singer]]'' in which he was a celebrity judge. They talked to each others family and got married on 27 August 2010 at a ceremony held in [[Chennai]].<ref name=\"TNIE2\">{{cite news|title='Bala is very caring'|url=https://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/malayalam/2012/may/07/bala-is-very-caring-365545.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[The New Indian Express]]|date=7 May 2012}}</ref> They were residing in [[Palarivattom]], [[Kochi]].<ref>{{cite news|last=Raveendra|first=Rahul|title=The duplex flat of Bala & Amritha|url=https://english.manoramaonline.com/lifestyle/decor/the-duplex-flat-of-bala-and-amritha.html|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[Malayala Manorama]]|date=20 May 2015}}</ref> They are reported to have started living separately in 2015, and got legal divorce in December 2019. They have a daughter named Avanthika (born 2012) who lives with her.<ref>{{cite news|title=Actor Bala, singer Amritha officially divorced|url=https://english.mathrubhumi.com/movies-music/movie-news/actor-bala-singer-amritha-officially-divorced-1.4348608|accessdate=24 February 2020|work=[[Mathrubhumi]]|date=9 December 2019}}</ref> Beside music, she is also a travel enthusiast.<ref name=\"travel\"/>\n\n==Discography==\n===Playback singer===\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n! Year\n! Song\