{"title_page": "Poornima Indrajith", "text_new": "{{short description|Indian actress}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2018}}\n{{Use Indian English|date=December 2018}}\n{{Infobox person\n| name          = Poornima Indrajith\n| image         = Poornima at 60th Filmfare Awards South (cropped).jpg\n| image size    = 220\n| caption       = \n| birth_name    = Poornima Mohan\n| birth_place   = <!-- Do not add without citing a reliable source -->\n| othername     = Anu\n| occupation    = Model, actress, television anchor, dancer, columnist, dubbing artist, fashion designer, entrepreneur\n| yearsactive   = 1997\u2013present\n| parents       = Mohan, Shanthi\n| spouse        = [[Indrajith Sukumaran]] (2002)\n| birth_date  =  <!-- Do not add without citing a reliable source -->\n| children      = Prarthana, Nakshathra\n| relatives     = Priya Mohan (Sister)<br/> \n[[Sukumaran]] (Father-in-law)<br/>[[Mallika Sukumaran]] (Mother-in-law)<br/>\n[[Prithviraj Sukumaran]] (Brother-in-law)\n| homepage      =\n| notable role  = \n}}\n\n'''Poornima Indrajith''' ([[n\u00e9e]] '''Mohan''') is an [[Indian people|Indian]] [[actress]], [[Fashion Designer]], [[television anchor]] and [[talk show host]] who acted in [[Malayalam cinema|Malayalam]] television serials and films.\n\n==Career==\n\nShe started her career as a [[model (profession)|model]] and then went on to host the music countdown show ''Pepsi Top Ten'' on [[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]]. She acted in many successful television serials such as ''Oomakkuyil'', ''Sthree oru Santhwanam'', '' Venalmazha'', ''Nizhalukal'' and ''[[Kolangal (TV series)|Kolangal]]'' in Tamil. She has also acted in a few movies, including ''[[Meghamalhar]]'', ''[[Valliettan]]'' and ''[[Randam Bhavam]]''. She received the best supporting actress award for her role in ''Meghamalhar''.\n\nIn late 2000s she returned toto hosting with the show ''Mega Swarnamazha'' in [[Surya TV]]. Later she hosted the successful television shows like ''Kadha Ithu Vare'' , ''Idavelayil'' ,''[[Kuttikalodano Kali]]'' and ''Made for each other season 2'' on the channel [[Mazhavil Manorama]]. She has appeared in many [[advertisements]] too.\n\nShe is a talented [[dancer]] also. She has now become a [[fashion designer]]. She runs a boutique by the name \"Pranaah\" in [[Kochi]]. She writes a regular column named \"In Style\" for \"Chithrabhumi\", a supplement of [[Mathrubhumi]].\n\n==Personal life==\n\nShe is born to Mohan and Shanthi, in a Kerala settled [[Tamils|Tamil]] family. Her mother tongue is Tamil. Her father is a practising lawyer and her mother runs a dance school.<ref>{{cite web |title=\u0d0e\u0d28\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d41\u0d02 \u0d38\u0d4d\u0d28\u0d47\u0d39\u0d24\u0d4d\u0d24\u0d4b\u0d1f\u0d46 \u0d2a\u0d42\u0d30\u0d4d\u200d\u0d23\u0d3f\u0d2e |url=http://www.nostalgiamag.in/details.php?cat=&id=379 |website=Nostalgia mag |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140217202457/http://www.nostalgiamag.in/details.php?cat=&id=379 |archivedate=17 February 2014 |language=Tamil}}</ref> She has a younger sister Priya Mohan, who is also an actress.<ref>{{cite news|first=Keerthy |last=Ramachandran |title=Second innings for Priya Mohan |url=http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/kochi/second-innings-priya-mohan-457 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120718091418/http://www.deccanchronicle.com/tabloid/kochi/second-innings-priya-mohan-457 |archive-date=18 July 2012 |newspaper=Deccan Chronicle|accessdate=5 November 2012}}</ref>\n\nPoornima is married to Malayalam actor [[Indrajith Sukumaran]]. She has two daughters, Prarthana and Nakshatra.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.hindu.com/fr/2007/06/01/stories/2007060151940400.htm|title=Striking a balance|date=1 June 2007|newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|accessdate=15 May 2010}}</ref> She is the daughter-in-law of the famous Malayalam actor late [[Sukumaran]] and actress [[Mallika Sukumaran]]. Malayalam actor [[Prithviraj Sukumaran]] is her brother-in-law.\n\n==Filmography==\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\" border=\"2\" cellpadding=\"4\" cellspacing=\"0\" style=\"margin: 1em 1em 1em 0; background: #f9f9f9; border: 1px #aaa solid; border-collapse: collapse; font-size: 95%;\"\n|- bgcolor=\"#CCCCCC\" align=\"center\"\n!  Year !! Film !!  Role !! Director \n|-\n|2020||''[[Thuramukham]]''|| {{TBA}} || [[Rajeev Ravi]]\n|-\n|2019||''[[Virus (2019 film)|Virus]]''|| Dr.Smrithy Bhaskar|| [[Aashiq Abu]]\n|-\n|  2015 || ''[[Double Barrel (film)|Double Barrel]]'' ||Voice for Laila ([[Swathi Reddy]]) ||[[Lijo Jose Pellissery]] \n|-\n|  2008 || ''[[Gulabi Talkies]]'' || ||[[Girish Kasaravalli]]\n|-\n|  2001 || ''[[Dany (film)|Dany]]''  || Madavi || [[T. V. Chandran]] \n|-\n|  2001 || ''[[Meghamalhar]]'' ||Rekha  ||[[Kamal (director)|Kamal]]\n|-\n|  2001 || ''[[Unnathangalil]]'' || Julie  ||[[Jomon (director)|Jomon]] \n|-\n|  2001 || ''[[Randaam Bhavam]]'' ||Akhila  || [[Lal Jose]] \n|-\n|  2001 || ''[[Naranathu Thampuran]]'' ||Sridevi ||[[Viji Thampi]] \n|-\n|  2000 || ''[[Valliettan]]'' ||  Lakshmi ||[[Shaji Kailas]] \n|-\n|  2000 || ''[[Varnakkazchchakal]]'' ||Sridevi/Cheeru  ||[[Sundar Das]]\n|-\n|  1999 || ''[[Cotton Mary]]'' ||Receptionist||Ismail Merchant, Madhur Jaffrey \n|-\n|  1997 || ''[[Kadhalukku Mariyadhai]]'' ||  Latha ||[[Fazil (director)|Fazil]]\n|-\n|  1997 || ''[[Innalekalillaathe]]'' || Maya||George Kithu \n|-\n|  1986 || ''[[Onnu Muthal Poojaym Vare]]'' ||Voice bit presence ([[Geethu Mohandas]])  ||[[Reghunath Paleri]] \n|-\n|}\n\n==Television and online career==\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable\"\n|-\n!Year\n!Program\n! Channel\n!Role\n!Language\n! Notes\n|-\n|2019|| ''Jimikki Kammal''|| [[Asianet News]]||Guest||Malayalam||Talk show\n|-\n|2019|| ''Innathe Cinema''|| [[Mazhavil Manorama]]||Guest||Malayalam||Talk show\n|-\n|2019|| ''Asiavision Awards''|| [[Asianet (TV channel)|Asianet]]||Guest||Malayalam||Award show\n|-\n|2019|| ''Asianet News''|| asianetnews.com||Guest||Malayalam||Talk show\n|-\n|2019|| ''Morning Show''|| Twenty Four||Guest||Malayalam||Talk show\n|-\n|